CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 21, 1939, pg. 17, reads: "Pittsburgh 'Y' Wins Thrilling Court Duel From Commandeurs - Pittsburgh's Strong Center Ave. 'Y' Team - Rated one of the strongest quintets to represent Pittsburgh in a number of years, the Center [Centre] Avenue 'Y' team, pictured above, will play in Detroit and Cleveland Saturday and Sunday. This team defeated the Philadelphia Commandeurs last week, 47 to 30. - Courier photo."
TitMainTitle: Centre Avenue YMCA basketball team wearing "Pitt Y" jerseys, possibly including Red Dorman standing third from left, and coach Charles "Teenie" Harris standing on left, in Centre Avenue YMCA
